HEADWORD: Cymous
<hw>Cy"mous</hw>
<pr>(s?"m?s)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>cymosus</ets>
full of shoots: cf. FF. <ets>cymeux</ets>. See Cyme.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the nature of a cyme, or derived from a
cyme; bearing, or pertaining to, a cyme or cymes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

